quran[11]{c,v,t}:
  3,122,"Two of your troops then lost heart, but God was their protector, and in God the believers should put their trust"
  3,123,"God helped you at Badr when you were weak, so be conscious of God, so that you may feel grateful"
  3,124,"Remember you said to the faithful, “Is it not enough for you that God helps you with three thousand angels sent down"
  3,125,"“Yes, if you remain firm, and do right, even if the enemy ambushes you, your Lord would help you with five thousand unrelenting angels.”"
  3,126,"God made it a message of hope for you, and an assurance to your hearts. There is no help except from God, the Exalted, the Wise"
  3,127,"He might cut off a fringe of the unbelievers or expose them to dishonor, and they will then be turned back, defeated"
  3,128,"Not for you, but for God, is the decision. Whether He turns in mercy to them, or punishes them, for they are indeed wrongdoers"
  3,129,"To God belongs all that is in the heavens and on earth. He forgives whom He pleases and punishes whom He pleases, but God is Oft-Forgiving, Mercifully Redeeming"
  3,130,"O you who believe, do not take usury, doubled and multiplied, but be conscious of God that you may flourish"
  3,131,Be aware of the fire which is prepared for those who do not believe
  3,132,"And follow God and the messenger, that you may obtain mercy"